Class SharedWriteProtectablePropertyListImpl

    • fr.cnrs.iees.properties.impl.SharedPropertyListImpl
      • fr.cnrs.iees.properties.impl.SharedWriteProtectablePropertyListImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PropertyListGetters, PropertyListSetters, ReadOnlyPropertyList, SimplePropertyList, SimpleWriteProtectablePropertyList, fr.ens.biologie.generic.DataContainer, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Sizeable, fr.ens.biologie.generic.WriteProtectable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class SharedWriteProtectablePropertyListImpl
extends SharedPropertyListImpl
implements SimpleWriteProtectablePropertyList

    Implementation of SimplePropertyList.

    1. Storage of properties: keys are shared (and stored outside this class), values are stored locally.
    2. Optimisation: memory and speed. No checks on dimensions, names or anything else.
    3. Use case: For large numbers of objects sharing the same set of properties and when a fine control of property list edition capability is needed.

    Properties and keys are stored in arrays so that property keys always come in the same order.

    The value of a property can only be changed if the list is in the 'writeEnable' state. The current state of the list is known by calling isReadOnly(). The state can be changed using writeEnable() and writeDisable().

    Author:
    J. Gignoux - 14 f√©vr. 2017
